wikipedia_page.main: Harold Roxbee Cox, Baron Kings Norton (6 June 1902 – 21 December 1997) was a British aeronautical engineer.  He was notable for his contributions to British industry, particularly aeronautical engineering, and for his part in the establishment of Cranfield University.
